body.p:
The Repositories view allows you to define and manage  repository
      locations and browse repositories. Repository files and folders are presented in a tree view
      with the repository locations at the first level, where each location represents a connection
      to a specific repository. More information about each resource is displayed in a tabular form:

Date - Date when the resource was last modified;

Revision - The revision number at which the resource was last
          time modified;

Author - Name of the person who made the last modification on the
          resource;

Size - Resource size on disk;

 Lock information - Information about the lock
          status of a file. When a repository file is locked by a user the  icon is displayed in this
          column. If no icon is displayed the file is not locked. The tooltip of this column
          displays the details about lock:

owner - the name of the user who created the lock;

date - the date when the user locked the file;

expires on - date when the lock expires. Lock expiry policy is set in the repository
              options, on the server side;

comment - the message attached when the file was locked.


Type - Contains the resource type or file extension.
